SIMPLE: kink
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kink
<hw>Kink</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>kink</ets> a
bend or turn, or Sw. <ets>kink</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A twist or loop in a rope or thread, caused by a
spontaneous doubling or winding upon itself; a close loop or curl; a
doubling in a cord.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An unreasonable notion; a crotchet; a whim; a
caprice.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Cozzens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kink</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Kink
<hw>Kink</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Kinked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Kinking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To wind into a kink; to knot or
twist spontaneously upon itself, as a rope or thread.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kink</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Kink
<hw>Kink</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Chincough</er>,
<er>Kink-haust</er>.]</ety> <def>A fit of coughing; also, a convulsive
fit of laughter.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kinkajou</ent>⟦br⟧
